  image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: c84817def6f01274d87eea09f2a6320f, type: 3}
  fact: Earth wears its own sunscreen! High up in the air, a special gas called Ozone
    absorbs dangerous ultraviolet (UV) light from the Sun. Without this layer, we
    would get a bad sunburn from being outside for as little as 5 minutes!
